2. Getting an element by class name:
Returns all elements having the same class name
. Getting an element by className() – method returns an html collection object
An html collection is an array like list of html elements
Length property provides

Ex
<h1 class="a"> Harshitha</h1>
    <h1 class="b"> Manvitha</h1>
    <h1 class="c"> veena</h1>
<script>
Let x= document.getElementsByClassName(‘a’)
document.write (x)

EX :
<h1 class="a"> Harshitha</h1>
    <h1 class="b"> Manvitha</h1>
    <h1 class="c"> veena</h1>
<script>
Let x= document.getElementsByClassName(‘a’)
for(let i=; i<x.length ;i++){
Document.write(x[i])
}

1. Getting an element by id
h1 id=”a”> I AM HARSHITHA </h1>
h1 id=”b”>I AM MANVITHA  </h1>
<script>
let x=document.getElementById(‘a’)
document.write(x)

4.	Getting an element by tag name -  This method takes a tagname

<h1 class="a"> Harshitha</h1>
    <h1 class="b"> Manvitha</h1>
    <h1 class="c"> veena</h1>
    <h1 class="c"> Hema</h1>
<script>
let x=document.getElementByTagName(‘h1’)
document.write(x)
for(let i=; i<x.length ;i++){
document.write(x[i])
}

QUERY SELECTOR : 
QUERY SELECTOR – Used to select the methods by ClassName and TagName
. it selects only the first matching element

EX :
<h1 class="a"> Harshitha</h1>
   <h1 class="b"> Manvitha</h1>
<h1 class="a"> Harshitha srinivas</h1>

<script>
let x=document.querySelector(‘h1’)
document.write(x)
}

QUERY SELECTOR All :
Can be used to select html elements by its tag name or class name
It  returns a node list which is similar to array like object 


